-- Belgium Beats Croatia 2-1 to Claim Spot at 2014 Soccer World Cup
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-10-11T18:07:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-11/belgium-beats-croatia-2-1-to-claim-spot-at-2014-soccer-world-cup.html
Romelu Lukaku scored two goals as
 Belgium  defeated Croatia 2-1 to clinch a berth in the 2014
soccer World Cup.  The victory guarantees Belgium of finishing as the top team
in its qualifying group. The winners of each of the nine
European groups advance to next year’s 32-team tournament in
Brazil, while the best eight runners-up enter a playoff for the
continent’s remaining four spots.  Belgium is the third team to qualify from Europe, after the
Netherlands and  Italy . Germany and Switzerland will also claim
places in Brazil with victories tonight, while Russia can also
qualify.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  